did.unittitle: Rockefeller Foundation records, projects, SG 1.38 (A2013)

physdesc.extent: 390 standard record storage boxes. Including but not limited to: Boxes R3989-R4003, R4011-R4385.

did.langmaterial: Multiple languages contained in written material specific to country/region. Predominately written in English.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Records have received basic level 1 processing to establish initial intellectual and physical control of the holdings. Materials remain in original record cartons and folders.
This guide provides file level description. Each file may represent multiple folders.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Project files transferred to the RAC by Rockefeller Foundation, 2013.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Records are primarily arranged by Program, with some materials arranged by the RF traditional series numbers.
Records are arranged as received. Within folders, materials are primarily arranged in reverse chronological order.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Records more than 20 years old are open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC. RAC is unable to provide access to obsolete media and original digital media. In addition separated media may not yet have undergone stabilization procedures. When feasible, a digital surrogate may be created via special order. All applicable charges will apply.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Grant administration files and related materials.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Rockefeller Foundation has title, copyright, and literary rights in the collection, in so far as it holds them. Rockefeller Archive Center has authority to grant permission to cite and publish archival material from the collection.
